com.tractrac.model.lib.api.attachment

Interface IAttachable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ICompetitor, ICompetitorClass, IControl, IControlRoute, IEvent, IIdentifiable, INamed, IPathRoute, IPosition, IPositionSnapped, IRace, IRaceSerie, IRoute, ISegment, ITeam
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAttachable

    public interface IAttachable

    This interface adds functionality for attaching custom data to an object. One object that implements this interface, can be extended using attachments. All the objects of the model implements this interface.

    It is necessary to create an IAttachmentKey to attach an object. For the same attachment, the same key has to be used. The IAttachmentManager class has to be used in order to create a new IAttachmentKey.

    Author:
    Jesper Grooss
